The Rays had a second player sidelined due to COVID-19 reasons, as infielder Yandy Diaz on Saturday was placed on the injured list due to symptoms. Infielder/outfielder Vidal Brujan was called up from Triple-A Durham and added to the active roster in place of Diaz. Catcher Francisco Mejia was placed on the COVID injured list on Friday after testing positive. The Rays are set to take on the Red Sox on Saturday night, planning a bullpen day to cover their pitching. J.P. Feyereisen will start, and manager Kevin Cash said the team would be pleased if he could work two innings and they would “mix and match” from there, with most of the other nine relievers available. Here is the Rays’ lineup: And for the Red Sox, with Garrett Whitlock starting: • • • Sign up for the Rays Report weekly newsletter to get fresh perspectives on the Tampa Bay Rays and the rest of the majors from sports columnist John Romano. Never miss out on the latest with the Bucs, Rays, Lightning, Florida college sports and more. Follow our Tampa Bay Times sports team on Twitter and Facebook.